r01/data/sn83045293/00517012452/1920102601/0069.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_emmental_ver01:data:sn83045293:00517012452:1920102601:0069/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_emmental_ver01/data/sn83045293/00517012452/1920102601/0069.pdf", "segment_count": 10, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83045293/1920-10-26/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_emmental_ver01/data/sn83045293/00517012452/1920102601/0069.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_emmental_ver01:data:sn83045293:00517012452:1920102601:0069/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_emmental_ver01/data/sn83045293/00517012452/1920102601/0069.pdf", "segment_count": 10, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83045293/1920-10-26/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_emmental_ver01/data/sn83045293/00517012452/1920102601/0069.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83045293/1920-10-26/ed-1/?sp=1"], "batch": ["whi_emmental_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/wisconsin/", "2/united states/wisconsin/milwaukee/", "3/united states/wisconsin/milwaukee/milwaukee/"], "contributor": ["wisconsin historical society"], "date": "1920-10-26", "dates": ["1920-10-26"], "description": ["If an idea is true you cant suppress it and if it is false it does not need to be sup pressedit will suppress itselfHorace Traubel Vol 9No 274 FINDINGS BY VICTOR L BERGER La Follettes Mouthpiece The Capital Tinies Speaks In Unmistakable Terms About Kleczka and Staf ford Calls Kleczka a Renegade and Stafford an OldTime Tool of the Interests Says That Neither Is En titled to Progressive Votes We agree Under the caption Progre ssives for Election OnlyI find in The Capital Times Madison Senator R M La Follettes ac knowledged mouthpiece ths fol lowing The aid of progressives is be ing sought in Milwaukee for the election of John C Kleczka and William H Stafford to congress We are unable to see how these gentlemen can make any valid claim to the support of progressives on their records of the past few years Kleczka 1 is one of the long list of renegade progressives who slipped when the real test came In the days when everybody was progressive Kleczka was known as aLa Follette man He attained to considerable political prominence in his own locality through his identification with the progressive movement During the war no one"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-04-13T23:35:04.470Z", "group": ["ndnp/whi", "wisconsin-historical-society-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83045293/1920-10-26/ed-1/?sp=1", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_emmental_ver01:data:sn83045293:00517012452:1920102601:0069/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=292&w=230", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_emmental_ver01:data:sn83045293:00517012452:1920102601:0069/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=585&w=461", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:whi:batch_whi_emmental_ver01:data:sn83045293:00517012452:1920102601:0069/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1170&w=923", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/whi/batch_whi_emmental_ver01/data/sn83045293/00517012452/1920102601/0069.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 1, "language": ["english"], "location": ["wisconsin", "united states", "milwaukee"], "location_city": ["milwauke